Mercedes calls it "car-to-x communication" and it would warn a driver of obstacles, like an overturned truck ahead, or anomalies, like a car heading into oncoming traffic, before they can be seen. The German company is putting cars equipped with this technology on the road this year. It's all part of a push to make driving safer.
